idance (generate these snippets by default):\n- C / libxml2:\n  • Before parsing: xmlDisableExternalEntityLoader(); xmlSubstituteEntitiesDefault(0); xmlLoadExtDtdDefaultValue = 0; \n  • Parse without entity substitution and with no network: doc = xmlReadMemory(buf, len, NULL, NULL, XML_PARSE_NONET | XML_PARSE_NOCDATA | XML_PARSE_NOERROR | XML_PARSE_NOWARNING);\n  • Do NOT pass XML_PARSE_NOENT. Do not rely on external entity loaders.\n- Java (DOM/SAX/SchemaFactory):\n  • DocumentBuilderFactory f = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();\n    f.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);\n    f.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-general-entities", false);\n    f.setFeature("http://xml.org/sax/features/external-parameter-entities", false);\n    f.setXIncludeAware(false);\n    f.setExpandEntityReferences(false);\n  • For SAXParserFactory/SchemaFactory, set the same features and setProperty("http://javax.xml.XMLConstants/property/accessExternalDTD", ""); setProperty("http://javax.xml.XMLConstants/property/accessExternalSchema", "").\n- .NET:\n  • var settings = new XmlReaderSettings { DtdProcessing = DtdProcessing.Prohibit, XmlResolver = null }; using var r = XmlReader.Create(stream, settings);\n- Python:\n  • Prefer defusedxml (defusedxml.ElementTree.fromstring). If using lxml, use parser = etree.XMLParser(resolve_entities=false, no_network=true); and reject DOCTYPE.\n- Go:\n  • encoding/xml does not resolve external entities; still cap input size (io.LimitReader) and disable any custom external resolvers.\n\nAdditional safeguards:\n- Impose input limits (size, element depth, attribute count). Fail closed on limit violations.\n- Never pass user-controlled XML directly to XSLT. If XSLT is needed, disable reading from network or filesystem and forbid the document() function.\n- Log rejections generically. Do not echo attacker-controlled XML back in errors.\n\nThis policy requires the assistant to emit XML parsing code that disables external entities and network access, forbids DOCTYPE, avoids entity expansion flags, and enforces resource limits by default."],\n["Rules#6: Ensure that all exceptions are caught and handled appropriately. Use try-catch/try-with-resources blocks to manage exceptions and provide meaningful error messages or recovery mechanisms."],\n\n3. Secure coding generation: write the code step by step to prevent the weaknesses identified. Document why each security measure is necessary with inline comments\n4. Code review: review the generated code line by line to confirm there are no weaknesses.\n5. Secure code output: output the final corrected code only, inside the four code blocks.\n', 'temperature': 1}}
